<HEADLINE> Chirac Sends Message of Condolences to India on Train Clash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac has
sent a message of condolences to his Indian counterpart, Kocheril
Raman Narayanan, on the train clash which killed at least 280
people Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Please allow me to present to you my most sincere condolences
and express, in the name of myself and the French people, all my
sympathy in this tragic circumstance. In these difficult hours, we
also think about the injured and the families of the victims,"
said Chirac in the message made public Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Two trains clashed Monday morning in eastern India, killing
from 280 to 400 people, according to rescuers. 
