<HEADLINE> French Forecaster Not Optimistic About Eclipse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The French weather forecasting
institute Meteo-France said Wednesday that it is not optimistic
about the weather condition on the day of complete eclipse on
August 11.
</P>
<P>
"The conditions of observation of the eclipse don't look good
at this moment in so far as a generalized sunshine time is not
expected," said Meteo-France.
</P>
<P>
It said that the index of confidence for good weather is three
out of five, with five being the highest point of optimism.
</P>
<P>
From now on, Meteo-France will publish daily its forecast on
weather condition before the day of eclipse on Internet and
through a special telephone number -- 08 36 68 08 08.
</P>
<P>
France will be one of the countries to see the complete eclipse
at noon on August 11, which will be the first in 300 years.
</P>
</TEXT>
