<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African Car Sales Continue Upward Trend in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Total vehicle sales in South
Africa continued its upward trend in July when they were up by
11.8 percent compared with June, according to figures released
Wednesday by the National Association of Automobile Manufacturers
of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
However, the total sales for the month, 27,310 units excluding
Hyundai, were still 14.3 percent below the level a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Passenger car sales (17,549 units) were 16.8 percent weaker in
July 1999 than in July last year, but were 12.2 percent higher
than in June.
</P>
<P>
Sales of light commercial vehicles (8,862 units) in July were
8.9 percent lower than sales in 1998. Month-on-month sales grew
by 11 percent.
</P>
<P>
Sales of medium commercial vehicles fell by 14.7 percent in
July compared with July last year, but were 3.3 percent higher
than in June this year.
</P>
<P>
Heavy commercial vehicle sales were once again the worst
performing segment as sales fell by 17.4 percent in July (488
units) compared with 1998. Month-on-month sales, were, however,
19.3 percent higher. 
</P>
</TEXT>
