<DOCNO> XIE19990805.0035 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Opens Autitrust Probe Into Dutch-Finnish Merger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said
Wednesday that it has decided to open an in-depth inquiry into the
public bid by the Finnish bathroom producer Sanitec Ltd Oyj Abp of
the Dutch company N.V. Koninklijke Sphinx Gustavsberg.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU) executive body said the main area of
concern identified is the companies' combined strong position in a
number of ceramic sanitary ware products in the Nordic countries
including Norway, Finland, Sweden, Iceland and Denmark, where they
would account for over three quarters of the market, and in
Belgium, the Netherlands and Luxembourg, the Benelux countries,
where the concentration would lead to combined market shares above
50 percent.
</P>
<P>
The EU's antitrust regulators believe the new merger would
violate the European Union's competition law. Both Sanitec and
Sphinx produce and market bathroom products, but the proposed
acquisition could apparently lead to creation and strengthening of
their dominant positions in a number of product and geographic
markets, the commission said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
In particular, the new entity would obtain a very strong market
position with respect to several ceramic sanitary ware products in
the Nordic countries. In several products, the new entity would
have market shares between 10-20 times higher than its largest
competitors.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, given the two companies are market leaders now,
the commission believed the merger would eliminate the most
important competitors. It would also have strong position in a
number of ceramic sanitary ware products in the Benelux, the EU
executive body said.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission said it had to enter into a full
investigation based on current facts before approving the new
firm. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
