<HEADLINE> Europe Must Learn Kosovo Lesson: Robertson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 4 (Xinhua) -- British Defense Secretary George
Robertson, who has just been appointed as NATO secretary-general,
said Wednesday the lesson of the Kosovo conflict was that
Europe must enhance its own military capabilities.
</P>
<P>
"One of the clear lessons of the Kosovo conflict is the need
for Europe to enhance its military capabilities," Robertson told a
news conference in London held shortly after his appointment was
announced.
</P>
<P>
He also underlined the need for the Western alliance to work
closely with Russia.
</P>
<P>
"Relations with Russia -- and with Ukraine -- are going to be
enormously important," he said.
</P>
<P>
Robertson said the potential enlargement of NATO to include
countries of Eastern Europe would be an important part of his new
brief.
</P>
<P>
"There are a number of other applicant countries which clearly
have ambitions and aspirations to join and we've made it clear
that the door is not closed," he said.
</P>
<P>
NATO made Poland, Hungary and the Czech Republic its new
members earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Robertson said he expected to take up the appointment later
this year when current NATO Secretary-General Javier Solana takes
up his new post as the European Union's foreign policy
representative. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
