<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Creates Timber Forest of 10,000 Hectares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh created a timber forest
on 10,593 hectares and a strip forest on 7,390 kilometers during
the last fiscal year ending on June 30.
</P>
<P>
Environment and Forest Minister Sayeda Sajeda Chowdhury told
the inaugural function of a nursery here Wednesday that
Bangladesh's 17.5 percent of land might go under water due to the
rising temperature and sea level, she said.
</P>
<P>
The natural disaster must be contained through massive
afforestation, she stressed.
</P>
<P>
The government is determined to create new forests and plant
trees to maintain ecological balance, she said, adding that a
massive afforestation program is going on under 15 projects in the
country.
</P>
<P>
She called upon the people to participate in the country-wide
tree plantation program that began on June 15 and will continue
till September 15 this year.
</P>
<P>
In this South Asian country, forest covers less than 15 percent
of the total area, compared to a desirable proportion of 25
percent, and the forest acreage is declining at a faster pace. The
government has taken a series of measures including organizing a
three-month country-wide tree plantation drive every year to
maintain ecological balance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
