<HEADLINE> Exports of India's Export Zones Up 22 percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Exports in India's 7 export
processing zones (EPZs) grew by 22 percent in the first quarter of
the current fiscal year compared with the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
According to the commerce ministry, exports by the EPZs
amounted to 10.48 billion rupees (43 rupees=1 U.S. dollar) as
against 8.57 billion rupees recorded a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The EPZs are expected to achieve a total export turnover of 65
billion rupees in 1999-2000 as against 52.52 billion rupees in
1998-1999.
</P>
<P>
The impressive performance by the zones is largely due to a
series of steps taken by the commerce ministry to liberalize the
regulatory environment, focus on strengthening of infrastructure
in the zones and an improvement in the export outlook. 
</P>
</TEXT>
