<HEADLINE> LIFFE Trades 194 Billion Pounds Per Day In July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The nominal value of contracts
traded on the London International Financial Futures and Options
Exchange (LIFFE) averaged 194 billion pounds daily during July.
</P>
<P>
Hugh Freedberg, the LIFFE's chief executive, told a press
conference Wednesday that July saw a 5 percent year-on-year
increase in value from July 1998 and a 9 percent increase in all
short term interest rate products.
</P>
<P>
"The volume in the FTSE 100 Index, now traded on LIFFE
CONNECTtm, LIFFE's new electronic trading platform, saw an
increase of 21 percent in futures and 24 percent in options, year
on year," he added.
</P>
<P>
January to end July, the LIFFE traded 74,654,717 contracts.
Total exchange open interest, a key indicator of liquidity as well
as long term use of the market, increased to 6,302,267 contracts.
</P>
<P>
Open interest in Euro money market products at 2,318,486
contracts reflects a continuous upward trend, the chief executive
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
