<HEADLINE> European Markets Mixed At Dow Advance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The UK stock market suffered a
mixed and directionless session Wednesday, depressed by persistent
weakness in BT and other telecom stocks.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 index closed down 15.2 points, or 0.2 percent, at
6,235.4 while the Dow Jones Industrial Average was recording gains
of around 130 points.
</P>
<P>
The market was down 13 points mid-afternoon, so at best the
bourse's performance didn't deteriorate into the close.
</P>
<P>
British Telecom suffered from U.S. selling pressure, traders
said. A press report saying rival Telewest Communication is
expected to launch a high speed Internet service Thursday hit BT
hard.
</P>
<P>
Germany's shares closed marginally higher after an uneven day's
trade as a chemical-fueled rally in the afternoon pushed the
market into positive territory.
</P>
<P>
The Xetra Dax closed at 5,119.37, up 11.69 from Tuesday's
close, having traded in a range of 5,149.10 to 5,067.20.
</P>
<P>
Paris shares closed lower in a dull session, but off their lows
with a mixed early performance on U.S. indices creating volatility
late on.
</P>
<P>
The CAC-40 index closed at 4,326.2 points, down 28.55 or 0.66
percent. Volume for the day was 1.7 billion euros. 
</P>
