<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania's Population Continues Shrinking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The population of Romania is
shrinking, with birth rate plunging even deeper and mortality rate
becoming disquietly high.
</P>
<P>
According to the country's latest official statistics,
Romania's population is lower by 23.4 thousand people during the
first quarter of 1999, which lead to a negative increase of 4.2
per 1,000 inhabitants, from 2.9 per 1,000 during the same time
span, last year. Romania's population numbered 22.489 million at
the end of last year, a decrease of 37,000 from 1997.
</P>
<P>
Practically, between 1990-1998, Romania's population shrank by
700,000, the country scoring worst in Europe at many demographic
indicators.
</P>
<P>
During the first quarter of 1999, birth rate had dropped to
10.4 per 1,000 from 10.5 in 1998, one of the lowest in Europe. At
the same time, infant and general mortality remains quite high. In
this first quarter alone, the number of dead reached 81,087, 14.6
per 1,000, from 13.3 per 1,000, last year.
</P>
<P>
Infant mortality, the rate of children dying before their first
birthday, had dropped to 20 per 1,000 from 20.5 last year, but
remains one of the highest in Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
