Libya's efforts to convene an extraordinary African summit in
Tripoli next month, el-Sherif said. (BC-Egypt-Libya-Summit)
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- An Iraqi civilian was killed and two others were
injured on Wednesday in U.S. and British air raids on civilian
facilities in northern Iraq, an Iraqi military spokesman
announced.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that at 11:05 local time (0705 GMT), nine
formations of enemy warplanes coming from Turkish airspace
violated northern Iraqi airspace over the provinces of Dohuk,
Erbil and Neineva, the Iraqi News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The warplanes attacked civilian facilities in the region,
causing the casualties, said the spokesman. (BC-Iraq-US Attack)
</P>
