<HEADLINE> IDB Finances Road Improvements in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) announced on Wednesday the approval of 146 million U.S.
dollars in loan to improve the road network in the state of Bahia,
Brazil.
</P>
<P>
The project consists of the paving of approximately 840
kilometers of roads and the improvement of another 1,420
kilometers through rehabilitation, maintenance, or reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
The state Department of Transportation infrastructure will be
strengthened in its administrative, planning, traffic safety, and
environmental management capacity, the IDB said.
</P>
<P>
The program will reduce transportation costs of the state's
road system and contribute to the overall economic and social
development of Bahia, said the IDB.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of project is 244 million dollars. The IDB loan
is for a 20-year term, with a five and a half year grace period,
at the variable annual interest rate, now at 6.98 percent. 
