<HEADLINE> Fighting Displaces More People in Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The latest fighting in
Afghanistan has pushed tens of thousands of people out of the area
north of Kabul and into the Panshir valley, United Nations sources
said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
U.N. agencies are in the process of finalizing a contingency
plan to provide food, medicine and other items to 100,000 affected
people in the Panshir valley, said U.N. spokesman Fred Eckhard,
quoting a UNHCR report as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to UNHCR, or United Nations High Commissioner for
Refugees, Afghanistan is the largest refugees source in the world,
with some 2.1 million Afghans in Iran and 1.6 million in Pakistan.
</P>
