<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Japan External Trade
Organization (JETRO) will host an exhibition in Tokyo this year to
promote the business links between Japan and African countries.
</P>
<P>
The "African Exhibition" will be held from October 28 to
November 1, to introduce the current situation of Africa and
African products, the Japanese trade organization said in a
newsletter distributed here this week.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will also promote mutual understanding at the
private level and encourage African countries to export goods to
Japan, the organization said.
</P>
<P>
It said it has invited 52 countries, 30 of which have
officially confirmed to participate in the exhibition.
</P>
