Countries which will have an exhibition area as large as 75
square meters include Tanzania, Egypt, Kenya, Mauritius and South
Africa.
</P>
<P>
The show is a follow-up of the resolutions of the Second Tokyo
International Conference for Africa Development which was
organized by the Japanese government last October. The conference
was attended by dignitaries from African countries and donors.
</P>
<P>
The Japan External Trade Organization is a non-profit
government- oriented organization chartered in 1958. Its mission
is to support trade between Japan and other countries, aiming at
promoting harmonious trade and investment. 
