<HEADLINE> Meningitis Epidemic Hits Northeastern Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Over 400 people have been taken
ill with meningitis since the beginning of last July in
northeastern Romania.
</P>
<P>
According to the Preventive Medicine Department in the Romanian
Health Ministry, 156 cases have been reported in Iasi county
alone. Of the 135 cases in Suceava county, 66 have been
acknowledged clinically, with the remaining 69 being diagnosed as
a combination of virosis and meningitis.
</P>
<P>
The causes of the epidemic have not been traced yet. Expert
teams of the ministry are assessing the situation on the spot, the
official Rompres news agency reported on Wednesday, adding that
Iasi and Suceava have set up an epidemic regime.
</P>
<P>
Experts at Bucharest's Ion Cantacuzino Institute and Iasi-based
Institute for Public Health collected samples to accurately assess
the diagnosis. Water samples and mosquitoes, which are believed to
carry the disease, have also been under investigation.
</P>
<P>
Meningitis has also occurred in other counties, as well as the
capital city of Bucharest. Efforts are being made to contain the
epidemic, trace the causes and treat the patients.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
