<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Open Nighttime Shenzhen-HK Ferry Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Shekou Harbor, in south China's
coastal city of Shenzhen, is to open nighttime ferry services to
Hong Kong in the middle of this month.
</P>
<P>
The number of people from Shekou entering and exiting Hong Kong
in 1998 surpassed 800,000, double the figure in 1990. More
employees of foreign-funded companies in Hong Kong have bought
housing in Shekou, and need to travel frequently between the two
areas, and a nighttime ferry service will help to relieve the
congestion.
</P>
<P>
There are 24 two-way ferry trips a day between Shekou and Hong
Kong, with the last one leaving at 18:30. The two nighttime ferry
trips will operate from 18:30 to 22:30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
