<HEADLINE> Shanghai Holds Record Number of International Exhibitions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 5 (Xinhua) -- This, China's leading industrial
city and financial center, has sponsored a total of 63 large
international exhibitions in the first seven months of this year,
up 1.5 times over last year's same period.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Shanghai Customs said the figure indicates
that his city opened a large international exhibition every three
days, on average.
</P>
<P>
The official said that, apart from traditional trade fairs and
exhibitions featuring industrial products, the international
exhibitions also covered the fields of resources, environmental
protection, insurance, nuclear industry and information.
</P>
<P>
He said the International Automobile Fair held in June alone
attracted over 300,000 visitors.
</P>
<P>
Experts here said that the large number of international
exhibitions probably means that the other Asian countries have
begun to recover from their financial crises, and domestic
economic growth is witnessing steady growth.
</P>
<P>
They stressed that Shanghai's promotion of its economic
exchanges worldwide is another important reason.
</P>
<P>
So far, Shanghai arranges over 40 regular international
exhibitions annually, involving automobiles, computers,
electronics, telecommunications, domestic electrical appliances,
ships, flowers, advertising, food and other industries.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the boom in international exhibitions is
also encouraging the development of local transportation,
telecommunications, hotels and advertising.  
</P>
</TEXT>
