<HEADLINE> Improved Coffee Variety Transplanted in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia, one of the third
largest coffee producers in Africa, is making effort to increase
its coffee production by popularizing improved coffee variety.
</P>
<P>
More than 8.6 million high-yield and disease-resistant coffee
seedlings have been transplanted in Oromiya State over the last
fiscal year ending on July 8, coffee development expert Belay
Garuma said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Oromiya is the biggest state in Ethiopia, which is
administratively divided into nine states.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia, with more than 300,000 hectares of acreage under
coffee, produces about 250,000 tons of coffee annually, one third
of which are exported abroad.  
</P>
