<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 5 (Xinhua) -- World No. 1 cyclist Laurent
Jalabert left hospital Thursday and may be back racing in time for
next month's Tour of Spain.
</P>
<P>
The French rider entered Madrid's Ramon y Cajal Hospital Sunday
after falling in the opening stage of a Spanish regional tour,
from which he suffered fractures to the skull and collarbone.
