<HEADLINE> Relics Museum to Be Built at Summer Palace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A modern museum will be built at
the Summer Palace, the largest imperial park in Beijing, to better
protect the 40,000 precious historic relics kept there.
</P>
<P>
The museum, which is already in the last phase of construction,
will be opened to the public before National Day, October 1.
</P>
<P>
Located on the east shore of Kunming Lake, the museum covers a
total floor space of more than 7,000 sq m. It is a two-story
building, built in the same style as the other ancient structures
in the park.
</P>
<P>
The Summer Palace, or Yihe Yuan, was built in 1750, and covers
a total area of 290 ha. It was put on the World Heritage list by
the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural
Organization, last year.
</P>
<P>
At the moment, only a fraction of the 40,000 historic relics
kept in the park is on show; the rest are stored in an old
warehouse.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
