<HEADLINE> Medical Fee Service Network Set up in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A service network has been set up
in China for the first time, offering prompt service in paying
medical fees and other services for its members.
</P>
<P>
The network, set up by the Orient Zhongbao Science and
Technology Development Co. Ltd., will send the fees for hospital
emergency service to its members within 24 hours on receiving a
request, so as to ensure they get timely medical treatment when
they get injured in traffic accidents.
</P>
<P>
Management personnel of the company said that the service will
spare its members the trouble of negotiating with the insurance
companies for compensation.
</P>
<P>
The network will also provide other services including
insurance consultation, free accident insurance and Internet hotel
bookings in some 70 cities around the country. The annual
membership fee is 198 yuan (about 23 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The network, quite common in developed countries and regions,
has been put into operation in over 40 cities, including Beijing,
Tianjin, and Shanghai, so far, and around 500 people have
registered for membership, according to the company staff.
</P>
</TEXT>
