<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Urged to Advocate Science </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The Falun Gong cult took
advantage of people's desire for good health to spread
superstition and defraud people, including women. With the
deepening struggle against Falun Gong, more women now have a clear
understanding of the true purpose of this illegal organization,
and have broken away from it, a Xinhua commentator said today.
</P>
<P>
The Falun Gong incident makes us realize that it is an
important duty of women's organizations to help women improve
their overall quality and establish a right viewpoint, which is
also a long-term task for Chinese women's activities, the
commentator points out.
</P>
<P>
"Women should arm their minds with scientific theories and
knowledge, and play key roles in advocating science and fighting
against superstition," continues the commentator.
</P>
<P>
Science is always opposite to superstition, and attitudes
toward science and superstition can decide the fate of a nation.
Only by advocating a scientific spirit can we improve our overall
national strength and provide a solid base for a socialist system
with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
"Women's fate is always closely connected with that of their
country," notes the commentator. The two decades since China's
opening to the outside world proves that women emancipated
themselves only by having confidence in the leadership of the
Communist Party, Marxism, and science.
</P>
<P>
It is the ultimate role of women to uphold science and break
away from superstition, and also their glorious mission.
</P>
<P>
Women account for half of China's population, and are a vital
force for pushing forward economic development and social progress.
</P>
<P>
The commentator points out that women play an irreplaceable
role in families. "If every family can employ a civilized and
healthy lifestyle, and reject all superstition, all of society
will form an atmosphere which will advocate science and reject
superstition."
</P>
<P>
The All-China Women's Federation issued a circular recently
calling on all women to take action and break away from Falun Gong.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the diligent, brave, and intelligent Chinese
women have enthusiasm to study modern science, uphold modern
culture, and make contributions to the country's bright future",
the commentator concludes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
