<DOCNO> XIE19990805.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Postpones Repatriation of Alien Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Foreign workers in 18 types of
businesses in Thailand's 37 provinces are allowed to work in the
country for three more months before being replaced by local
labors, Labor and Social Welfare Minister Wuth Sukosol announced
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
About 86,000 alien workers are eligible to extend their working
service in Thailand thanks to a recent cabinet resolution, the
Thai News Agency quoted the minister as saying.
</P>
<P>
During the 90-day extension period starting from Thursday,
governors and employment officers in the 37 provinces are
requested to launch fact-finding missions to seek first-hand
information on the employment situation of the alien workers.
</P>
<P>
Alien workers may be allowed to work after the 90-day period
expires provided that their employers report to provincial
authorities that their businesses are shunned by Thai workers and
the claim is verified, according to the minister.
</P>
<P>
Since the financial crisis in mid 1997, Thailand has been
trying to alleviate the worsening unemployment situation by
repatriating alien workers and replacing them with local ones.
</P>
<P>
However, few local laborers were willing to take the relatively
harder-working and less-paid jobs, like carrying rice packs. In
August last year, the government had to postpone the repatriation
of foreign laborers for one more year till August 4 this year.
</P>
<P>
So far, some 200,000 Thais have come up to register at
provincial employment offices, who can then replace alien workers
to be repatriated after the three-month postponement, Wuth said.
</P>
<P>
He added that illegal alien workers, if arrested, would be
immediately and unconditionally sent back to their home countries
after August 4.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that more than 2 million people in Thailand are
out of job as a result of the two-year-old financial and economic
crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
