<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Euro-Zone Economic Confidence Improves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)'s 11-
country euro-zone showed clear improvement in business and
consumer confidence in July this year, a survey published on
Thursday said.
</P>
<P>
The consumer confidence indicator rose in the euro-zone in July
while remained constant in the 15-nation European Union as a whole,
said the survey conducted by the EU's executive branch, the
European Commission.
</P>
<P>
"This can to a large extent be attributed to the important
improvement observed on the consumer confidence in most countries
and to the fact that consumers are more optimistic about the
general economic situation in the future," the survey said.
</P>
<P>
Confidence in the industrial sector rose consistently in both
the euro-zone and the EU, following the positive trend beginning
in March, said the survey, noting that France, Italy and Germany
in particular contributed to this improved situation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, capacity utilization in industry maintains a similar
level with the two previous quarters, the survey said.
</P>
<P>
Managers expect the capacity constraints to decrease
appreciably and the outlook for new orders and exports is
optimistic, it said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the construction confidence indicator was
stable for the EU and slightly increased for the euro-zone,
according to the survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey also pointed out that there have been less
optimistic data from other countries, especially from Italy,
Greece and Denmark.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the survey concluded that the economic confidence
indicator for July shows a significant increase for the euro-zone
and a slight improvement for the 15-member EU region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
