<HEADLINE> Pavarotti to Hold Concert in Bucharest on Eclipse Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The famous Italian tenor
Luciano Pavarotti is to hold a concert in Bucharest on August 11,
the total solar eclipse day.
</P>
<P>
"It was not at all difficult for me to make up my mind and come
to Romania and I am quite delighted I am to hold a concert in
Bucharest," the famous Italian tenor told the local Ziarul
Financiar Daily on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It was not only this impressive phenomenon that made Pavarotti
give up his holiday and come to Romania but also the fact that "
the Romanian musicians are very talented and generous and the
Romanian audience are warm and open."
</P>
<P>
The Italian tenor also praised the strong cultural and social
ties between Romania and his country and was touched with the fact
the Romanians spoke Italian very well. Pavarotti loves Romania for
another reason --- it creates great musicians and soccer players.
</P>
<P>
To build a high stage where Pavarotti is to sing, more than 230
tons of metal are to be used by around 200 workers to put up the
whole scaffolding. As many as 22,000 chairs will be set there,
and 16,000 of them will be specially bought for this concert, seen
as a great musical event.
</P>
<P>
The Eclipse on August 11 can be best seen from Romania's
territory, although it is to be visible from no less than 16
countries. The Eclipse's climax will be also in Romania, nearby
southern town of Ramnicu Valcea.
</P>
<P>
The Eclipse will attain its widest visibility stripe measuring
about 112 km. Bucharest is to be the only capital city in the
world right in the middle of the eclipse's shadow stripe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
