<HEADLINE> State Council Orders Freeze of Forest Land Use for Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The General Office of the State
Council issued a notice recently, requiring a freeze on the use of
forest land for construction projects before the adoption of the
Regulations for the Implementation of the Forestry Law.
</P>
<P>
The notice stipulates that during the freeze period, local
governments at all levels must take effective measures to strictly
ban the use of forest land for construction projects.
</P>
<P>
It says that illegal forest land users or those who exceed
their power to grant forest land use will be punished.
</P>
<P>
The State Forestry Administration is also urged to supervise
the forest land use in the country, with the help of local
departments concerned.
</P>
<P>
The notice says the State Council is drafting the Regulations
for the Implementation of the Forestry Law to wipe out illegal
forest land use.  
</P>
</TEXT>
