<HEADLINE> Nepali Carpet Export to U.S., Britain Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Nepal's carpet export to the
United States and Britain increased markedly in fiscal 1998/99,
raising hopes that these two countries would become potential
export markets for Nepalese carpet in the future, the Kathmandu
Post reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said data compiled by the Carpet and Wool
Development Committee show that carpet export to the United States
and Britain grew by 26.3 percent and 24 percent respectively in
the 1998/99 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Germany remained the largest consumer of Nepal-made woolen
carpets and imported nearly 2 million square meters of woolen
carpets in the year, accounting for 76 percent of Nepal's total
export.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Britain consumed only 9 percent and 3
percent of the total export respectively. Belgium was the third
largest export destination for Nepal's carpets, taking 4 percent
of the total carpet export.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland, Austria and the Netherlands are other major buyers
of Nepal's carpets.
</P>
<P>
Diversifying export destinations is a long cherished dream of
Nepali carpet exporters. With the rising export growth to the
United States and Britain, Nepali carpet exporters and
manufacturers are one step further near this goal, the newspaper
said.
</P>
<P>
Woolen carpet has remained the largest exportable item of Nepal
for the last decade. During 1998/99, carpet export earned over 149
million U.S. dollars for Nepal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
