<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, Pakistan, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Karachi stocks plunged
Thursday by 2.26 percent due to the news that the chief of Hub
Power Company (Hubco) was leaving Pakistan without holding any
meeting with the government officials.
</P>
<P>
The news depressed the market which resulted in panic selling
as people felt that the power tariff dispute between the largest
private power producing company and the government will need
longer time to resolve, dealers said.
</P>
