<HEADLINE> People's Daily Article Criticizes Li Hongzhi's Fallacies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- China's leading newspaper, the "
People's Daily", will carry a commentator's article tomorrow to
further criticize the fallacies of Li Hongzhi, head of the illegal
organization Falun Gong.
</P>
<P>
Li has used two important methods to run the Falun Gong cult
and its organizations which include poisoning practitioners' minds
with fallacies and controlling practitioners through various
levels of organization, the article points out.
</P>
<P>
Though the fight against the Falun Gong cult has mitigated the
bad effects of the fallacies of Falun Gong or Falun Dafa, the
pernicious influence of Li Hongzhi and his fallacies is still
alive among some of his followers, and needs to be eradicated, the
article says.
</P>
<P>
The article stresses that we should help those who are still
following the fallacies of Li Hongzhi including some Communist
Party members, cadres and intellectuals, to analyze how they went
astray, find the ideological reasons for this, and provide them
with education and instructions accordingly.
</P>
<P>
The process of refuting the fallacies of Li Hongzhi is also a
process of promoting education in Marxist materialism and atheism,
and the basic principles and guidelines of the Chinese Communist
Party, the article says.
</P>
<P>
The fight against Falun Gong will not only help the Falun Gong
practitioners, but the Chinese people as a whole to improve their
political awareness and their immunity against fallacies all kinds.
</P>
<P>
Party organizations at all levels should recognize the
importance and difficulty of the serious ideological and
theoretical combat against Falun Gong, and try to improve Party
members' ideological and theoretical studies. 
</P>
