<HEADLINE> Sensex Down 43 Points in Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index fell down
by about 43 points Thursday on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) due
to heavy bull unloading despite fresh purchases from Foreign
Institutional Investors.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share sensitive index opened firm at 4,669.78, to
the intra-day high of 4,688.99.
</P>
<P>
However, bulls later resorted to unloading their long
positions, adversely affecting the sentiment and as a result, the
sensex dropped to a low of 4,588.96 before closing at 4,601.19 as
against Wednesday's close of 4,644.07, netting a loss of 42.88
points or 0.92 percent.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index dropped by 18.23 points to 2,018.20 from the
previous close of 2,036.43.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the Dollex were quoted remarkably down at
459.26 and 176.18 compared with the previous close of 463.28 and
177.89 respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
