relations with neighboring countries, the foreign minister said:
"The government... has already achieved success in securing due
share of the Ganges water (with India) and bringing peace to the
Chittagong Hill Tracts (in southeastern Bangladesh)."
</P>
<P>
"The government's sincere efforts and equally position response
from the leaders of neighboring nations are contributing to the
solution of issues, one after another," he said, hinting at Prime
Minister Sheikh Hasina's initiative in defusing tension in the
sub-continent following nuclear explosions by India and Pakistan
in May last year. 
