<HEADLINE> Macao to Implement Compulsory Schooling for Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Macao will put into effect a decree
which stipulates that the guardians of children from five to 15
years old are duty-bound to make the latter receive schooling.
</P>
<P>
The decree was drafted by the Education and Youth Department of
the Macao government and was discussed at a local consultative
committee. It is expected to be approved in the middle of the
month.
</P>
<P>
The department will give admonition to those violating the
decree, and those who ignore admonitions several times can be
prosecuted. Penalties may be one to five years in prison in
accordance with the Criminal Law of Macao.
</P>
<P>
The department's director Luis Amado de Viseu said that
compulsory schooling will be carried out in two stages. All
children of the right ages must study at primary schools by the
year 2002 and then compulsory education will be implemented among
children of older ages.
</P>
<P>
The director noted that the department will provide assistance
to the families in difficulty to ensure that all children attend
proper schooling. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
