<HEADLINE> HK Trade Development Council Launches Market Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A Market Day of the Hong Kong
Trade Development Council (TDC) opened Thursday at the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Under the theme of "Advancing into Millennium with TDC One-Stop
Service," the two-day event unveiled global business opportunities
offered by TDC's 300 trade promotional activities.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, Victor Fung, chairman of the
TDC, said the TDC is committed to upgrading and expanding its
services to help Hong Kong companies expand their market reach and
enhance their global competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
"Quality customer service will be the key part of our future
work. The 'One-Stop Service' Pavilion set up at this year's TDC
Market Day is our initial move towards this direction," Fung said.
</P>
<P>
The "One-Stop Service" Pavilion is tailored for local small and
medium-sized companies wanting to expand their exports and enhance
their business knowledge.
</P>
<P>
TDC marketing advisors are ready to discuss with visitors about
their needs and advice them on the best mix of TDC services that
can help them expand their business overseas.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony, Fung also announced the inauguration
of TDC Service Center, which is a one-stop shop that provides Hong
Kong companies with information on TDC services.
</P>
<P>
Fung said that through the Market Day activities, Hong Kong
companies can grasp more industry information and market
intelligence so that they can make use of knowledge to increase
their competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
Held concurrently with the Market Day are 29 free seminars at
which government officials, market experts and business
professionals discuss the latest trade issues relating to the
Chinese mainland market, information technology and e-commerce,
overseas markets and innovative businesses in Hong Kong.
</P>
</TEXT>
