<HEADLINE> Gold Price in Hong Kong Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong
gained one HK dollar to close at 2,377 HK dollars a tael on
Thursday, according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 257.04 dollars a troy ounce, 0.
09 U.S. dollars up from the previous close at Thursday's exchange
rate of one U.S. dollar against 7.7623 HK dollars.
</P>
