<HEADLINE> World Leading Online Broker to Open Business in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 5 (Xinhua) -- TD Waterhouse, a world leading
online broker, announced here on Thursday that it will launch
local stock trading during the fourth quarter of 1999 and
electronic trading in the first quarter of 2000.
</P>
<P>
Approved by the Council of the Stock Exchange of Hong Kong (
SEHK) and the Securities and Futures Commission, TD Waterhouse is
the first foreign discount broker to open share trading service in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
TD Waterhouse has also acquired a seat of the SEHK from a
leading Hong Kong brokerage, Harvester (Securities) Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
"Local trading will allow us to offer the Hong Kong market to
our two million clients around the world." said Andrew Nevin,
managing director of TD Waterhouse Hong Kong, at the press
conference.
</P>
<P>
"Given the importance of the Hong Kong market, we know that
many of these customers will take advantage of this capability."
he added.
</P>
<P>
As the second largest discount broker in the world, TD
Waterhouse has operations in Canada, the United States, Hong Kong,
Australia and Britain.
</P>
<P>
The company provides Internet-based investing services and
related financial products, and has over 2.8 million customers
accounts and 113 billion U.S. dollars in assets under
administration.
</P>
<P>
Stephen D. McDonald, Chief Executive Officer of TD Waterhouse,
said, "Adding stock trading in Hong Kong is an important step in
our global strategy of being a significant player in every market
we enter."
</P>
<P>
"The Internet is revolutionizing the brokerage industry and TD
Waterhouse is at the forefront of these changes," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
