<HEADLINE> CAAC Blasts Lee Teng-hui's Splittist Remarks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The General Administration of
Civil Aviation of China (CAAC) today blasted Lee Teng-hui of
Taiwan for his splittist remarks.
</P>
<P>
"Lee's 'two-states' statement has severely undermined relations
between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits," and "endangered the
motherland's peaceful reunification," CAAC officials said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
It is known to all that there is only one China in the world
and Taiwan is an inseparable part of China's sacred territory. "
Though the two sides have not re-united, Taiwan's status as part
of Chinese territory has not changed at all," they said.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the Chinese mainland has made unremitting
efforts for the relaxation of relations between the two sides and
the promotion of the process of eventual peaceful reunification of
the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Civil aviation circles on both sides of the Straits have also
contributed greatly to this effort in order to realize direct
flight between the two sides at an early date.
</P>
<P>
Lee's "two-states" statement has seriously undermined the basis
of contacts and exchanges between the two sides, hurt the feelings
of the entire Chinese nation, and cast a heavy shadow over the
realization of "three exchanges": exchanges of direct mail service,
trade, air and shipping services, the CAAC said.
</P>
<P>
It is the general wish of the entire nation to solve the Taiwan
issue, realize the "three exchanges," and bring about the eventual
peaceful reunification of the motherland, they noted.
</P>
<P>
"We call on our counterparts in Taiwan to contribute to the
maintenance of and adherence to the 'One China' principle, and to
the promotion of the process of eventual reunification of the
motherland," they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
