<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Meets Congolese Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
Monday met Congolese rebels of the Congolese Rally for Democracy
(RCD - Goma faction) in the rebel stronghold of Goma, rebel
sources said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
''It's true we had fruitful discussions with the Ugandan
president,'' Moise Nyarugabo, RCD Vice-President, told Rwanda News
Agency in a phone interview.
</P>
<P>
He said that RCD officials explained to the Ugandan president
the process in which former RCD leader Ernest Wamba dia Wamba was
removed from power and replaced by Emile Ilunga.
</P>
<P>
''He seemed to be convinced by our explanations. We handed him
documents relating to Wamba's removal and we hope that they will
be examined seriously,'' Nyarugabo further said.
</P>
<P>
''At the end of the discussions, we noted that President
Museveni had been given a false report,'' Nyarugabo underlined.
</P>
<P>
Uganda has been supportive of Wamba since he was ousted from
power in May 1999. Wamba continued to claim to be the legitimate
leader of the rebel movement and contended with his rival for the
signing of the Lusaka cease- fire agreement.
</P>
<P>
The RCD officials said they were ready for endorsing the accord
once the issue of Wamba whom they say represent only himself and
not the movement will have been solved.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, a Zambian delegation led by the
Minister in Charge of Presidential Affairs, Eric Silwamba, is
expected in Goma and Kisangani where it will investigate on the
balance of power between the so- called Goma and Kisangani
factions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
