<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Telecom to Launch ImageOnline Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The U.S.- based film giant
Kodak and the Cable and Wireless of Hong Kong Telecom (HKT)
announced here Thursday their decision to jointly launch the
ImageOnline service as a step towards the e-commerce expansion.
</P>
<P>
"ImageOnline is a breakthrough in the information world," said
Clifton Hanaoka, regional business general manager and vice
president of Kodak Business Imaging Systems, Great Asia Region.
</P>
<P>
It delivers faster and more integrated document management and
work flow applications for the business community to boost their
efficiency and profitability, he added.
</P>
<P>
ImageOnline allows companies and public sector organizations to
maintain a virtual digital library, through which they can
instantly access images, data and documents stored in digital form.
</P>
<P>
Information is customized and categorized in specific formats
and distributed through Cable and Wireless HKT's broadband network.
</P>
<P>
Marisa Leung, director of Corporate Market of Cable and
Wireless HKT, said: "ImageOnline is one of the new iCommerce
solutions under the umbrella of our Com21 initiative launched
earlier this year, which provides integrated communications
solutions to help enterprises stay ahead of the competition."
</P>
<P>
Subscribers only need access to a Web browser-equipped personal
computer to log into ImageOnline's totally secure remote server to
access the information they need. The system is accessible anytime
and anywhere in the world with information capable of being
transmitted, shared and managed anywhere electronically.
</P>
<P>
As the world's first on-demand imaging service offered through
a broadband network, ImageOnline will cater to the needs of
organizations with intensive document demands, such as government
departments, accounting, legal, insurance and transportation firms.
</P>
</TEXT>
