<HEADLINE> Tibet Enjoys Cool Weather This Summer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- As heat waves hit many parts of
China this summer, the Tibetan Plateau is experiencing pleasant,
cool weather, blue skies, and fresh air.
</P>
<P>
According to the local weather bureau, the temperature in Tibet
has been remained between 10 and 20 degrees centigrade since the
beginning of the summer due to the plateau's high altitude and
plentiful rainfall.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, temperatures in Beijing and other parts of
northern China have been as high as 40 to 42 degrees centigrade,
causing many people to suffer from heatstroke.
</P>
<P>
Lots of rain this year has make the plateau much greener this
summer, and even the usually barren hills have turned green,
making it easier for livestock to thrive in the grasslands.
</P>
<P>
The pleasant temperatures have also attracted more tourists
from home and abroad, particularly from inland cities.
</P>
<P>
"It's so nice to go out and enjoy nature here. In Beijing, I
just stay in my air-conditioned room all day long," one visitor
from the capital told Xinhua.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
