<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
closed firmer Thursday, buoyed by stronger performances in the
resource and finance sectors.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index ended 13.2 points higher at
3,018.9, falling back from a 25-point gain earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
On the local bourse, the all resources index rallied 21.0
points on the back of firmer commodity prices.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index added 10.1 points to 5,214.1 with the
help of renewed buying in the banking sector.
</P>
<P>
The bank index bounced 51.3 points higher to 6,348.1, with
gains across the "big four" players.
</P>
<P>
The Commonwealth Bank was the star performer, surging 50 cents
to 24.70 Australian dollars, a gain of more than 2 percent.
</P>
<P>
ANZ climbed 12 cents to 10.75 Australian dollars, Westpac
lifted 6.9 cents to 9.932 Australian dollars and National
Australia Bank firmed 3.7 cents to 23.33 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 415.09 million stocks traded for 1.1
billion Australian dollars (726 million U.S. dollars). Falling
stocks edged out rising stocks 596 to 590 and 453 remained steady.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
