<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Bounces Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar bounced
higher Thursday, briefly touching 66 U.S. cents after a
significant hike in commodity prices overnight.
</P>
<P>
The Australian currency finished the day at 65.63 U.S. cents
from 65.48 at Wednesday's close.
</P>
<P>
During the day it reached 66 U.S. cents and dipped to 65.60.
</P>
<P>
In the money market, the 90-day bank bill rate was 4.87 percent
from 4.92 percent on Wednesday and the 180-day bill was 4.97
percent from 5.03 percent.
</P>
<P>
Also at the local close, the Australian dollar was buying
0.6102 euro from 0.6089 at Wednesday's close and 75.17 Japanese
yen from 75.56. 
</P>
</TEXT>
