<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed broadly lower Thursday on continued
selling by foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 13.54
points to 705.98, recovering from the day's low of 686.30 recorded
in the early afternoon session.
</P>
<P>
The all-share Emas index shed 3.93 points to close at 180.91
points, the Industrial Index fell 31.81 points to 1,204.23 and the
Second Board Index lost 2.89 points to 151.64.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 583 to 142 while 86 counters were
unchanged and 109 counters untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover decreased to 460.160 million shares
valued at 1.124 billion ringgit (295.789 million U.S. dollars)
from Wednesday's 526.357 million shares valued at 1.097 billion
ringgit (288.684 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
