<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Hopes to See Peace and Stability on Korean Peninsula </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official said
Thursday that China sincerely hopes to see peace and stability is
maintained on the Korean peninsula.
</P>
<P>
Qian Yongnian, head of the Chinese delegation, told the sixth
plenary session of the four-party talks on the peninsula here, "to
this end, the Chinese side put forward some propositions and
proposals in previous meetings and has made active and earnest
preparations for this meeting."
</P>
<P>
In particular, China has studied the outline of peninsular
peace regime based on full consideration of the characteristics of
the peninsula and all parties' concerns, said Qian, who is also
chairman of the current round of the talks also attended by
representatives of the United States, the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea and the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
Qian said, "We stand ready to discuss with other parties in
relevant subcommittee meetings the initial conception and
preliminary plan of the Chinese side and at the same time we are
looking forward to in-depth discussions by all parties on tension
reduction and confidence building measures on the peninsula in
search of common ground."
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that the current round of talks could build
on the previous rounds that began in the late 1997 and witness
more pragmatic and deeper discussion so that some ways could be
found that suit to the prevailing conditions on the peninsula and
will facilitate the settlement of the issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
