<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Denies Seeking Nuclear Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A senior Saudi official has denied
that Saudi Arabia is seeking nuclear weapons from Pakistan or
other countries.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Second Deputy Premier Prince Sultan Ibn Abdul-Aziz said
that his country was a signatory of the Nuclear Non-proliferation
Treaty and committed to its international obligations, the
London-based Saudi daily Al Charq Al Awsat reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Prince Sultan, who is also minister of Defence and Aviation,
asserted that Saudi Arabia hopes to see the region free of all
mass destruction weapons, including nuclear arms.
</P>
<P>
Press reports had quoted British sources as saying that Saudi
Arabia could be seeking to possess nuclear arms in an agreement
with Pakistan, citing the great attention given to prince Sultan's
visit to Pakistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
