<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Police in Northern China Uncover Stolen Relics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Police in north China's
Hebei Province have uncovered 114 pieces of stolen relics in one
of the province's counties and have arrested two suspects.
</P>
<P>
The relics, dating back to the Warring States period (475-221 B.
C.) and the Han Dynasty (206 BC-220 AD), were found some days ago
in a mini-bus as the two men were driving across Shexian County in
Hebei on their way to east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The two apparently stole the relics in north China's Shanxi
Province, next to Hebei, and were trying to smuggle them into
Shandong's port city of Weihai, police said.
</P>
<P>
This operation was part of a police campaign to crack down on
smuggling and ensure safety in the province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
