<HEADLINE> Malaysia Launches Web Site to Counter Negative Reports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Thursday launched a
Web-site called "My Malaysia" aimed at promoting nation-building
among Malaysians and countering negative reports about the
country.
</P>
<P>
"My Malaysia" web-site was created because negative reports
about the country disseminated through the Internet could
undermine efforts to revive the economy, attract tourists and
bring about prosperity to the people, its Chairman Awang Had
Salleh said.
</P>
<P>
"Negative reports can poison the people's minds and turn them
to be anti-establishment," he was quoted by the Malaysian national
news agency Bernama as saying.
</P>
<P>
The web-site launched by Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad in
Miri, Sarawak, East Malaysia, formed part of efforts to counter
lies and provide an alternative channel to the various slanders
existing in web-sites, Awang said.
</P>
<P>
The web-site, located at http://www.mymalaysia.com.my, provides
a one-stop channel for users to gather accurate information and
facts on Malaysia, focusing on politics, economy, tourism, human
&AMP; social rights, as well as science, technology &AMP; environment.
</P>
<P>
Its main highlights are "Topics of the Week" and "News Trends"
which cover write-ups on selected weekly topics of discussion and
comments on current Malaysian issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
