<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia-Namibia Border Closed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Namibia has closed its border with
Zambia at Katima Mulilo near Sesheke in Zambia's Western Province
following conflict in the area between the Namibian government and
a rebel group.
</P>
<P>
Zambia also closed its border a day after the Namibian
government closed the other side, Zambia Daily Mail newspaper
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Home Affairs Minister Peter Machungwa confirmed the closure. He
said the border had been closed because Namibia had earlier closed
its side of the frontier.
</P>
<P>
Machungwa explained that every border has two sides and closure
of the Zambian side was a consequence of the Namibian side being
closed.
</P>
<P>
"It's not from our side and we have nothing to do with what is
going on there, we closed the border because our side could not
function with the other side closed," he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister acknowledged the clashes that had taken place on
the Namibian side and said the Zambian government was studying the
situation.
</P>
<P>
He advised Zambians living around the border area not to panic
because the government had taken measures to ensure their
security.
</P>
<P>
The government had not received reports on any Zambian joining
the conflict on either side of the border, he said.
</P>
<P>
Also there had been no refugees received from Namibia by
Wednesday as a result of the conflict that erupted two days ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
