<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed higher here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index was 12 points higher at 2,190 with a turnover
of 80 million NZ dollars (43 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leading stocks, Telecom rose 16 cents to 865 cents,
Carter Holt Harvey 10 to 247 cents, Auckland Airport 4 to 310
cents, and Fletcher Building 1 cent to 279 cents.
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Energy fell 19 cents to 523 cents, Sky TV 10 to 350
cents, Telstra 8 to 1,000 cents, Fletcher Paper 7 to 143 cents,
and The Warehouse 2 to 722 cents.
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Forests closed unchanged at 105 cents. 
</P>
