<HEADLINE> Kenyan Police Arrest 130 Foreign Suspects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Police in Kenya's capital Nairobi
have arrested 130 Somalis and Ethiopians in a major crackdown on
illegal aliens, the Kenya Times newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The foreigners were suspected to be involved in criminal
activities including armed robberies, carjackings and drug
peddling, Nairobi Provincial Police chief Peter Mbuvi said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The suspects were arrested in their hide-outs in a raid which
started at 2 am and ended 9 am Wednesday morning, Mbuvi added.
</P>
<P>
The police were sorting out the suspects with a view to
arraigning them in courts before they are repatriated to their
respective countries.
</P>
<P>
Mbuvi also revealed that police discovered two pistols and 60
rounds of ammunition from the aliens during the swoop.
</P>
<P>
Admitting that increasing crime rate was of great concern,
Mbuvi said regular patrols have been intensified across the city
to ensure that all suspected criminals are brought to book.
</P>
<P>
The police chief said the operation will be extended to other
parts of Nairobi until the confidence of city residents is
restored on their safety and security.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Office in Nairobi has warned its visitors
against walking in the center of the city at night even for the
shortest distance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
