<HEADLINE> 57 Multinationals in South China's Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Fifty-seven of the world's top
500 multinational corporations have made investments in this south
China city, capital of Guangdong Province, according to local
sources.
</P>
<P>
These companies include General Motors, Exxon, Mitsubishi,
Marubeni, and Royal Dutch-Shell.
</P>
<P>
Multinationals have invested in 93 projects in Guangzhou
involving a combined investment of two billion U.S. dollars and
ranging from petrochemicals, electronics, light industry, and
telecommunications to automobiles and motorcycles.
</P>
<P>
While striving to improve its investment environment, Guangzhou
has been intensifying efforts to attract overseas investors over
the past several years.
</P>
<P>
By June, Guangzhou was home to 8,000 overseas-financed
businesses with total investments of 47.7 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
