<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibet Getting More Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Some 118,000 people from China and
abroad visited China's Tibet Autonomous Region in the first half
of this year, a 28.6 percent increase from the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
There were 25,018 overseas visitors, an increase of 30.9
percent, according to the local tourism administration. Earnings
from tourism amounted to 68.5 million yuan for the period, up 5.6
percent, and 8.16 million U.S. dollars, up 35.5 percent. The
tourist business paid 2.728 million yuan in taxes, up 2.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
To attract more tourists, the region sponsored two 15-day
training classes during the 6-month period to provide more
qualified guides and a promotion campaign at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The region expects to have 403,000 tourists this year,
according to local tourism officials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
