<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WB-Funded Generator Passes State Quality Appraisal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A large-scale generating unit
funded with loans from the World Bank (WB) has passed a state
quality appraisal and has been formally accepted by the State
Power Corp. of China after seven months of trial operations.
</P>
<P>
The 600,000-kilowatt unit, installed at the No.2 Power Plant in
the city of Yangzhou in east China's Jiangsu Province, has the
capacity to generate three billion kwh of electricity annually.
</P>
<P>
The unit, which cost about nine billion yuan to build, is the
first 600,000-kilowatt generator in east China accepted by the
State Power Corp..
</P>
<P>
The plant is now building another generator with the same
capacity.  
</P>
</TEXT>
