<HEADLINE> Death Toll Rises to 288 in Indian Train Tragedy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The death toll in Monday's
railway tragedy in West Bengal of India rose to 288 Thursday with
the recovery of one more body from the mangled coaches of the two
trains.
</P>
<P>
Northeastern Frontier Railway General Manager Rajendra Nath
said in Gaisal, West Bengal, that rescue operations were called
off early Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
No more bodies were likely to be found in the debris, officials
said. All the bodies have been shifted from the accident site to
the morgues at local hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Nath indicated that the tracks have been cleared and normal
railway services are likely to be resumed later in the day.
</P>
</TEXT>
