<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Has Diplomatic Ties With Over 70 Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has established diplomatic
ties with 78 countries all over the world and has opened 29
embassies, two permanent missions and two consulates-general in
various parts of the world, according to the first-ever Diplomatic
Handbook published by the Myanmar Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The newest Myanmar embassies were opened in South Africa and
Brazil, the first Myanmar diplomatic missions in Sub-Sahara Africa
and Latin America.
</P>
<P>
In keeping with the obligations of a member of the Association
of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), into which Myanmar was
integrated in July 1997, the country has embassies in all ASEAN
member countries. Likewise, all ASEAN countries have resident
embassies in Yangon, the handbook says.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to strengthen regional cooperation, Myanmar also
joined in August 1997 the BIST-EC, a regional economic grouping
initially comprising Bangladesh, India, Sri-Lanka and Thailand.
With the inclusion of Myanmar, the grouping was then renamed as
BIMST-EC. The five countries all border the Bay of Bengal.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Myanmar has been a U.N. member since 1948.
</P>
<P>
The handbook added that Myanmar's independent and active
foreign policy has served so well its national interest and the
policy would continue to be the pillar of the foreign relations of
the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
