<HEADLINE> China Reaps Good Summer Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- China's National Bureau of
Statistics is reporting summer grain yields this year of 118.49
million tons, the second highest figure in its history.
</P>
<P>
The bureau says that this summer grain output shows an annual
increase of 4.7 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attribute this good grain crops to good weather for
the latter growth period, bringing increases in per-hectare yields.
</P>
<P>
Because of dry spells last winter and new grain distribution
regulations, the amount of land sown in summer grain is 780,000
hectares less this year than in last year. The amount of land sown
in rapeseed has increased 3.4 percent to 6.39 million ha. and
yields are up 18.2 percent to 9.33 million tons, the bureau says.
</P>
</TEXT>
