<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Epizootic Experts Meet in Bulgaria on Blue Tongue Disease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- International epizootic experts and
relevant officials from the EU, Bulgaria and Greece met in the
Bulgarian city of Bourgas on Wednesday to discuss ways of
controlling the animal epidemic of Blue Tongue Disease found in
southern Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
The meeting called for a two-year ban on Bulgaria's export of
live animals, which does not include milk and dairy products.
</P>
<P>
The disease, originated in Africa, spreads through blood
contamination and turns the tongue of an affected animal into blue.
It normally does not affect human beings but the meat of an
affected animal is unedible.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria registered its first ever instance of Blue Tongue
Disease in the south-eastern Bourgas area last month. Within three
weeks, the disease was found to have spread to southern regions of
Yambol and Haskovo. More than 500 sick sheep have so far been
killed.
</P>
<P>
Experts fear that the epidemic may spread to neighboring Turkey
and Greece, and then to other European countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
