<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Orlando Set to Deal Penny Hardaway to Phoenix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Penny Hardaway appears close
to getting his wish to leave the Orlando Magic.
</P>
<P>
According to a local radio report, the Phoenix Suns are on the
verge of acquiring the disgruntled All-Star guard from the Magic
for forwards Danny Manning and Pat Garrity and a pair of first-
round draft picks.
</P>
<P>
However, a Suns official said today the Magic have not agreed
to the reported deal.
</P>
<P>
Hardaway had three years left on his current contract with
Orlando before exercising a clause that made the four-time All-
Star a free agent. As a result, the Magic would have to re-sign
Hardaway first and then deal him to Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
Chicago pulled the same ploy with Scottie Pippen last year when
it sent him to Houston.
</P>
<P>
Hardaway had become a lightning rod for criticism over the
Magic's limited success since the departure of superstar center
Shaquille O'Neal. He averaged 15.8 points, 5.7 rebounds and 5.3
assists per game during the lockout-shortened regular season, his
seventh in the league.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Hardaway spent most of the regular season
feuding with veteran coach Chuck Daly over handling the point
guard duties. He made no secret of his disdain for the media,
which he felt made him the scapegoat for the team's struggles.
</P>
<P>
Hardaway is in Orlando's top five of every all-time statistical
category with the exception of fouls committed. For his career, he
has averaged just over 19 points, just under five rebounds and
more than six assists per contest.
</P>
<P>
A first-round selection of the Golden State Warriors in 1993,
Hardaway was acquired by Orlando in a draft day deal involving top
overall pick Chris Webber. He teamed with O'Neal to lead the Magic
to the NBA Finals in 1995, when they were swept by the Houston
Rockets.
</P>
<P>
The Suns appear more than willing to deal two reserves after it
was believed they needed to give up forward Tom Gugliotta in any
trade to acquire Hardaway. Gugliotta averaged a team-leading 17
points and 8.9 rebounds a game last season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
