<HEADLINE> Dennis Mitchell Suspended for Using Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 4 (Xinhua) -- American star sprinter Dennis
Mitchell received a two-year suspension Tuesday for a failed drug
test but still is eligible for the 2000 Sydney Olympics, a local
report said today.
</P>
<P>
Mitchell contended that last year's positive result for high
levels of testosterone stemmed from drinking five beers and having
sex four times the night before the test, but an International
Amateur Athletic Federation arbitration panel rejected his appeal.
</P>
<P>
His retroactive ban from April 1, 1998, to March 31, 2000,
keeps the U.S. 100-meter champion from competing in this month's
world championships in Seville, Spain.
</P>
<P>
In Monte Carlo, Canadian sprinter Ben Johnson, stripped of his
gold medal and 100-meter world record for a positive steroid test
at the 1988 Seoul Olympics, was suspended for life in 1993 after a
second positive test. 
</P>
