<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentina Calls for Efforts to Defend, Promote Mercosur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President Carlos
Menem on Wednesday reiterated the need to defend and promote the
Southern Common Market (Mercosur).
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating the National General Attorney Office, the
president requested prompt and active support for "self-
institutionalization in this enormous region."
</P>
<P>
Menem said that in a dramatically changing world, "various
asymmetry situations have surfaced similar to the recent
experience in Mercosur," which comprises Argentina, Brazil,
Paraguay and Uruguay, with Bolivia and Chile as associated members.
</P>
<P>
He called for joint efforts from all walks of life to preserve
Mercosur, a regional trade block which covers some 200 million
people in an area of almost 13 million square kilometers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
