<HEADLINE> Cuba to Host Ibero-American Meeting of UNICEF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- An Ibero-American meeting of the
United Nations Children's Fund is to be held here on November 8-9,
the "Joventud Rebelde" newspaper reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Alfredo Missair, who is in charge of the organization in Cuba,
said the meeting -- "Summit of Infancy and Adolescence" -- would
have UNICEF backing.
</P>
<P>
"The fundamental idea of the summit is to put the topics of
infancy and adolescence back on the agenda of the Ibero-American
summits," said Missair.
</P>
<P>
Participants of the meeting have proposed a declaration with
its recommendations to the Ibero-American presidents, which will
be included in the final document. The final document will be
released at the end of the summit. 
</P>
