<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Deploy 42,300 Security Personnel to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The Police Headquarters in
Jakarta planned to deploy 423 companies consisting 42,300 men to
safeguard the General Session of the People's Consultative
Assembly (MPR) which will be held later this year.
</P>
<P>
"The security personnel will comprise 150 companies from the
police and 273 companies from the military," Jakarta Deputy Police
Commander Brig. Gen. Sutanto was quoted by the Antara News Agency
Thursday as saying.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Police Headquarters will also deploy 118
companies of civilian guards in the capital city's five
municipalities to support the police and military personnel, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Governor of Jakarta Sutiyoso said that his office will hold a
meeting with local public figures for talks on the MPR general
session.
</P>
<P>
He also called on all parties to maintain security, to enable
Jakartans to carry out their daily and routine activities in
peace.
</P>
<P>
The MPR, the country's highest decision-making body, will meet
from October to elect the country's next president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
