<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Hold Trade Fair in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar will hold a trade fair in
Bangkok, Thailand from August 11 to 14, aimed at stimulating trade
between the two countries, official newspaper The New Light of
Myanmar reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar Trade Fair'99, sponsored by the country's
Cooperative Department and the TTF Co. of Thailand, will be
attended by a total of 134 delegates from nine cooperatives and 15
private companies.
</P>
<P>
They will put on display their products of gems, rattan,
electrical goods, furniture, gold and silver tapestry, silk salon,
Thanakha (Myanmar traditional cosmetic) and soft drinks.
</P>
<P>
In last December, a first Thai trade exhibition, sponsored by
the Department of Export Promotion of the Thai Ministry of
Commerce in collaboration with its Myanmar counterpart, was held
in Yangon under the Myanmar-Thai economic cooperation promotion
program.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Myanmar-Thai bilateral trade,
 including border trade, stood at 434.9 million U.S. dollars in
the fiscal year 1998-99 which ended in March, of which Thailand's
export to Myanmar amounted to 358.8 million dollars, favoring
Thailand in the balance of trade. 
</P>
