<HEADLINE> Moderate Earthquake Hits Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 4 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.5
on the Richter scale hit Argentina's San Juan and other northwest
provinces at noon on Wednesday .
</P>
<P>
The National Institute of Seismic Prevention said the tremor,
lasting some 30 to 40 seconds, did not leave any damage or victims.
The epicenter of the quake was at Sierra Pie de Palo, almost at
the center of the Province of San Juan.
</P>
<P>
In 1977, a strong earthquake of 7.4 degrees occurred with the
same epicenter. It nearly destroyed the city of Caucete. 
</P>
