<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Military Conducting Combat Training in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A group of U.S. military personnel
are carrying out combat training in the jungle area in eastern
Ecuador, near the shared border with Colombia, said an Ecuadorian
military sources on Wednesday who requested anonymity.
</P>
<P>
The sources declined to reveal the number of the North
American "Jungle Brigade" and denied that the training in the
Ecuadorian Jungle Warfare School formed part of a U.S. plan of
intervention in Colombia to help fight the guerrilla groups.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadorian defense ministry kept silent when the Colombian
newspaper "El Espectador" published an article earlier, which said
that the special forces from the United States were being prepared
for jungle warfare for future combat against the Colombian
guerrilla forces.
</P>
<P>
But the sources revealed that military personnel from Brazil,
Colombia, Bolivia, Central American countries and the United
Kingdom also received the same kind of training at the same school,
adding that their presence is only temporary and the trainees will
return to their countries of origin when the training is completed.
</P>
<P>
He said that this type of training has been taking place since
the armed conflict between Ecuador and Peru in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990805.0350 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sotomayor Confirmed Positive in Sample B </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
But the world and Olympic champion himself said through the
Cuban delegation that he is totally innocent and would appeal the
Pan American Sports Organization (PASO) decision to withdraw the
gold medal from him.
</P>
<P>
"I am very sad to come here to give you sad news, " PASO
president Dr. Mario Vazquez Rana told the reporters at a news
conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The Pan Am Games laboratory in Montreal had been "carefully and
thoroughly" analyzed the urine samples from the Cuban athlete and
traces of Cocaine were found in both A and B samples, Dr. Rana
said.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Eduardo de Rose, chairman of the PASO Medical Commission,
said the amount of Cocaine in Sotomayor's urine is what is usually
found in a person who takes this kind of drugs and it is a very
recent case which must have taken place in the last four or five
days.
</P>
<P>
Now it is up to the International Amatueur Athletics Federation
(IAAF) to decide the sanction of Sotomayor.
</P>
<P>
Cocaine is a stimulant drug which is very easy to be detected
and whose time of stimulation is very short. It was put at the top
of the banned drug lists of the International Olympics Committee (
IOC) since they began to conduct drug tests in 1967.
</P>
<P>
At another news conference later, Cuba acted defiantly by
declaring Sotomayor is "an innocent and dignified man" who has
never taken any banned drugs and accusing there exists some kind
of sabotage and conspiracy against the Cuban athletes.
</P>
<P>
"Javier Sotomayor is a complete sports gentleman. He
participated over 60 games and all the test results have been
negative." said Mario Granda, chief doctor of the Cuban medical
group.
</P>
<P>
Sotomayor was very "surprised" and "upset" at the positive
results and totally rejected them, Dr.Granda said.
</P>
<P>
When asked about how to explain the traces of Cocaine in the
urine sample, he said:" We have no explanation. But we're sure
that this athlete has not in-taken this substance."
</P>
<P>
He went on to say there is a "manipulation" and "clear
intention to damage Cuba" in the Sotomayor case.
</P>
<P>
It would be impossible that a herbal tea, which contains a
large amount of Cocaine and which is often used by Cuban athletes
as a helpful medication, was responsible for Sotomayor's positive
results as some media outlets indicated, Dr. Granda said.
</P>
<P>
Because the medical group have analyzed everything which was
given to him in Cuba in the last ten days and found nothing could
be responsible for the positive results, Dr.Granda said.
</P>
<P>
There must have been something given to the athlete in his food
during his stay here in the athletes village accountable for the
Cocaine traces.
</P>
<P>
"He was in a trap, " Dr. Granda said.
</P>
<P>
When asked about whether the Cuban delegation has taken some
special measures to check the food in the next couple of days to
avoid what they called the sabotage against Cubans, the reply was
no.
</P>
<P>
"We don't have special measures. We don't blame anyone or any
organization." He said.
</P>
<P>
"Sotomayor is the example of the world-wide sports. He is not
only admired by athletes, by his own people, but by everyone
associated with the sports.
</P>
<P>
"He is completely innocent; for many years he has proved
himself trustworthy and we completely trust him." Dr. Granda said.
</P>
<P>
It seems incomprehensible that Sotomayor, an experienced
athlete who set the world record of 2.45 meters in 1993 and has
been the top man in the sport for over 12 years, made such a
simple and obvious mistake.
</P>
<P>
"Actually, it's a big surprise." the PASO chief Dr. Rana said,"
It might be the mistake from his physician." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
