<HEADLINE> France, Cuba Cooperate on Fight Against Cross-Border Crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- France will continue to work with
Cuba in its fight against cross-border crime after a latest police
dog training program between the two countries, a French diplomat
said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Francis Roudiere, a French Embassy official here, said
cooperation between the customs authorities of the two countries
has been successful and will go on with the sharing of other
techniques of combating drug-trafficking and terrorism.
</P>
<P>
The French Customs Department donated six police dogs to its
Cuban counterpart. The dogs are German Shepherds and Labrador
Retrievers, which will be employed in detecting drugs and
explosives.
</P>
<P>
Cuba, which relies on the tourism industry as its major income,
has strengthened border control to check trafficking of drugs and
explosives, which has been on the rise with the greater flow of
tourists. 
</P>
