<HEADLINE> Ecuador Closes Borders to Peru's Livestock and Meat Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Ecuadorian Ministry of
Agriculture and Livestock on Wednesday informed the Andean
Community of its decision to close its border with Peru to prevent
the spread of the livestock-affecting foot-and-mouth disease.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will also temporarily ban the entrance of products
and by-products of beef, mutton, goat and pork from Peru.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadorian Service of Agricultural Sanitation (SESA) urged
the country's ranchers to be on the alert to prevent Ecuadorian
livestock from being infected by the C-virus of the disease.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the SESA doubled its vigilance on its border with
Peru to prevent the entry of livestock, especially pigs, which are
the most likely carriers of the virus.  
</P>
