<HEADLINE> Uruguay to Propose Solutions for Mercosur Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay will make specific
proposals at the South American Common Market (Mercosur) meetings
for resolving commercial disputes within the bloc, the local press
reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Didier Opertti said that his country will
suggest setting up a technical secretariat for Mercosur to avoid
protectionist measures and coordinate the macroeconomics policies
in the sub-region.
</P>
<P>
The Uruguayan proposal was first raised last December and has
been accepted by other Mercosur members -- Brazil, Argentina and
Paraguay, which have also agreed to introduce mechanisms to avoid
frequent unilateral measures.
</P>
<P>
After the outbreak of the trade war between Argentina and
Brazil, Uruguay, the ad interim president of the bloc, has called
for a meeting of the Ministers Council, the highest political body
of Mercosur, scheduled for Thursday and Friday of next week.
</P>
</TEXT>
