<HEADLINE> Austria's Unemployment Down in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The number of Austria's unemployed
people in July dropped by 9.5 percent from the same month last
year with the national jobless rate down to 5.3 percent from 5.9
percent a year ago, according to statistics released by the labor
market service Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The number of jobless came to nearly 180,000 at the end of July,
down 9.5 percent from the figure in July last year and down 1.5
percent from the figure last month.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Health, Labor and Social Affairs Lore Hostasch
attributed the plunge in unemployment to the success of the
government's job policy, which she said brought jobs to more
people, especially women, young people and people above the age of
50.
</P>
<P>
Some experts credited the favorable employment situation on the
surge in business investment in Austria and seasonal reasons.
</P>
</TEXT>
