<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Slightly Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange
closed slightly down Wednesday with the Benchmark IPC index
reducing 35.18 points, or 0.68 percent, to 5,142.91.
</P>
<P>
Operators changed 68.260 million shares for about 140.208
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the peso, stood at 9.55 to one dollar for
sale and 9.25 for purchase in the main exchange houses of the
Mexico city, compared with 9.60 for sale and 9.25 for purchase on
Tuesday. 
